    <section class="aboutMain">
      <section class="aboutus-motto">
        <div class="aboutus-big-text">
          <p>
            Hey, We are the <strong>Red Explorers</strong> Brief History
            <span>About Us.</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="aboutus-sm-text">
          <p>
            At Red Explorers, we believe every journey tells a story. What
            started as a shared passion for discovery has evolved into a
            comprehensive guide for modern travelers. We are dedicated to
            uncovering the world's hidden wonders, sharing authentic cultural
            experiences, and providing the practical tips you need. Whether you
            seek adventure or relaxation, we are here to inspire your next great
            escape.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="aboutmain-sec-pic">
        <img src="/images/aboutus2.png" alt="people picture" />

        <p>
          Our team of passionate explorers travels the globe to bring you the
          most authentic and breathtaking experiences. From the highest peaks to
          the deepest oceans, we document every step of the journey to help you
          plan your own adventures. We believe that travel is not just about
          seeing new places, but about connecting with people and cultures. Join
          us as we continue to explore the unknown and share the beauty of our
          world.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="aboutArticles">
        <article class="ourStory">
          <h2>Our Story</h2>
          <p>
            It all began with a single backpack and a one-way ticket. What was
            meant to be a gap year turned into a decade-long pursuit of the
            extraordinary. Red Explorers was born from the realization that the
            best travel advice doesn't come from brochures, but from the people
            who have walked the path before you.
          </p>
          <p>
            Over the years, we have navigated through bustling souks in Morocco,
            trekked the silent glaciers of Patagonia, and shared meals with
            local families in rural Vietnam. These experiences shaped our
            philosophy: travel is about immersion, not just observation.
          </p>
          <p>
            We started this blog to document our journey, but it quickly grew
            into a community of like-minded adventurers. Today, we share our
            highs and lows, our mistakes and our triumphs, so that you can
            embark on your own journeys with confidence and curiosity.
          </p>
          <p>
            Join us as we continue to map the unmapped and tell the stories of
            the world, one destination at a time.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="whoAreRedExplorers">
          <h2>Who Are Red Explorers</h2>
          <p>
            We are a diverse team of writers, photographers, and digital nomads
            united by a love for the unknown. "Red" symbolizes the passion and
            energy we bring to every expedition, while "Explorers" defines our
            endless curiosity.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our team isn't just about visiting landmarks; we are about
            understanding the soul of a place. We believe in sustainable travel
            that respects local cultures and environments. We strive to leave a
            positive impact wherever we go, supporting local economies and
            advocating for responsible tourism.
          </p>
          <p>
            Whether we are reviewing the best gear for a hike or uncovering a
            hidden café in Paris, our goal is to provide honest, first-hand
            information. We are your scouts, your guides, and your friends on
            the road.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are Red Explorers. We don't just travel; we live the journey.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="aboutCameraMan">
          <h2>About Our Cameraman</h2>
          <p>
            Capturing the essence of a moment requires more than just a camera;
            it requires an eye for the unseen. Our lead visual storyteller,
            Alex, has spent over a decade documenting the raw beauty of our
            planet. From the vibrant colors of festivals to the quiet solitude
            of mountain peaks, Alex's lens brings our stories to life.
          </p>
          <p>
            With a background in documentary filmmaking, Alex focuses on the
            human element of travel. It's not just about the landscape; it's
            about the people who inhabit it. His work challenges us to look
            closer and appreciate the intricate details that make each culture
            unique.
          </p>
          <p>
            Through his photography and videography, we hope to transport you to
            these destinations, inspiring you to see the world with your own
            eyes.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="what-learn">
          <h2>What you’ll Learn Here</h2>
          <p>
            Red Explorers is designed to be your ultimate travel companion. We
            break down the complexities of planning a trip so you can focus on
            the experience. Whether you are a seasoned backpacker or a
            first-time flyer, our resources are tailored to help you travel
            smarter, cheaper, and deeper.
          </p>
          <h3>On Our Website You’ll find:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>> Comprehensive Destination Guides & Itineraries.</li>
            <li>> Budget Travel Tips & Money-Saving Hacks.</li>
            <li>> Cultural Etiquette & Language Basics.</li>
            <li>> Travel Gear Reviews & Packing Lists.</li>
            <li>> Photography Tips for Capturing Your Journey.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>
